File: The SABC says the claims are misleading and incorrect and that it's not meeting with the committee on this matter. JOHANNESBURG -The SABC is denying reports in the Sunday Times that it will be requesting more money from Parliament's Portfolio Committee on Communications and Digital Technology. The public broadcaster says the claims are misleading and incorrect and that it's not meeting with the committee on this matter. READ: Breakthrough in SABC, PSL battle The Sunday Times reports the SABC has projected a R 2-billion loss because of COVID-19. In a statement released on Sunday, the broadcaster admits the outbreak has had an impact on its advertising revenue, but says it has put measures in place to mitigate this.